Ordered from Mick O’Shea’s Irish Pub so many times now. From the salads to the sandwich, soups, to appetizers everything is delicious. The food is always fresh. I usually go with a sandwich but today I got a Cobb salad and the romaine, avocado, tomatoes, eggs, cheese, bacon, and chicken were all great quality. I’ve never found a hair in my food. This place is clean and they make their food with care. The shepherd’s pie...amazing and fresh. Jambalaya and cream of crab...you should try it yourself I bet you’ll re-order. The quality is great. The soups all have a good amount of food and high quality products going in. For what one is paying...especially ordering take out you can’t go wrong with an order from here. Thank you for making and caring for the food you serve.

O'Shea's is a true public house, with the freshest pour of Guinness in town, a menu to make you fat and happy, and enough good talk to make you stay for another round. Irish classics like the hearty Bangers and Mash or the Fish and Chips (with fish so flaky tender you'd be better off holding the whole piece wrapped in a newspaper if you could) never disappoint, but it's the people that really make this place. Whether you wear a suit or a helmet to work you'll find a welcome spot for you here. College kids come to kick back, AOH blue-hairs brunch here and local bands write sings about Mick's because this is everybody's pub. Stop in to say hello and the friendly, engaging staff will make you feel like you can keep coming back forever. I should know, more than 16 years after leaving Baltimore, I'm making the 270+ mile trip from NC to visit 3 or 4 times a year and I've still got a hug and a pint waiting for me when I arrive.
